Each mutant has: **ID · Class · Target · Mutation spec · Ground truth ·
Spec anchor / Design expectation · Expected sound finding ·
Reproduction · Recovery**. After application the Injector emits an
injection log with the exact diff per mutant; the orchestrator
verifies the log against this manifest before the Detector is
invoked.

### Notes on obfuscated test payloads in this manifest

Where this manifest needs to refer to an adversarial test payload
that the live `apex-prompt-guard.cjs` would itself block on write
(e.g. the prompt-injection probe in H-B2), the payload is
described in token form (the four leading words of the
role-hijacking phrase, individually capitalised, with their full
sequence reconstructed only at Phase-6 injection time). The
manifest never contains the live blockable sequence as a literal
on disk; the Injector re-assembles it from the token list when
constructing the test invocation.

### Anti-overlap discipline (vs working corpus)

This corpus was authored against `WORKING-CORPUS.md` to be
**concretely different** in target file and/or mechanism for every
class:

- **Class A (2):** target spec-named Auto-Continuity hooks
  (`memory-watchdog.sh`, `session-auto-resume.sh`) — NOT the
  spec-named guard hooks the working corpus deleted
  (`apex-prompt-guard.cjs`, `apex-workflow-guard.cjs`) and NOT the
  `apex-workflows/` directory rename. Different files, different
  spec anchor (Auto-Continuity Layer §407–414, not Defense-in-
  Depth axis-10).
- **Class B (2):** mechanism is NOT a magic-string allowlist (the
  W-B1/W-B2/W-B3 pattern). H-B1 is a regex-anchor weakening
  (word-boundary misuse) on a *different* guard
  (`path-guard.sh`); H-B2 is a case-folding gap on a *different*
  guard (`prompt-guard.sh`).
- **Class C (2):** target hooks NOT used by the working corpus:
  `comprehension-gate.sh` and `turn-checkpoint.sh` (W-C1/2/3 used
  `_state-update.sh`, `circuit-breaker.sh`, `session-log.sh`).
- **Class D (1):** target test is NOT `test-guards.sh` (W-D1) or
  `test-decision-mode.sh` (W-D2). Mechanism is NOT a tautology
  assertion (W-D1) or an early `exit 0` (W-D2) — it is `+ 0`
  swallowing of the per-file FAIL counter increment, so the test
  still runs to completion with no early exit and no obvious
  tautology.
- **Class E (1):** pattern is NOT a credential-shaped literal
  (W-E1) and NOT a dead-function-that-deletes-state (W-E2). It is
  a hardcoded localhost-only IP (`127.0.0.1`) baked into a
  network-egress helper's non-overridable default — a CI-breaking
  defect with no spec anchor.
- **Class F (2):** probes target different stages and aspects
  from W-F1/W-F2. H-F1 probes Step C (`batch-scheduler`)
  Deferred-section abuse, NOT Step B WONTFIX-justification
  (W-F1). H-F2 probes Step D (`wave-executor`) NEW-FINDINGS
  dual-sink (RESULT-embedded vs the standalone file), NOT Step E
  orchestrator-filename ingestion (W-F2).

